g(X)
 \mathbb E[Y | g(X)] \overset{def}= \mathbb E[Y | \sigma(g(X))] 
 \sigma(g(X)) = (g \circ X)^{-1}(\Sigma) = \{ X^{-1}(g^{-1}(S)) \, | \, S \in \Sigma \} 
 \{ X^{-1}(g^{-1}(S)) \, | \, S \in \Sigma \} = \{ X^{-1}(S) \, | \, S \in \Sigma \} = X^{-1}(\Sigma) = \sigma(X), 
 \mathbb E[Y|g(X)] = \mathbb E[Y | \sigma(g(X))] = \mathbb E[Y | \sigma(X)] = \mathbb E[Y|X]. 
 f_Y(y \, | \, g(X) = g(x)) = f_Y(y \, | \, X = x). 
 \mathbb E[Y | g(X)] = \int y f_Y(y \, | \, g(X) = g(x)) dy = \int y f_Y(y \, | \, X = x) dy = \mathbb E[Y | X]. 
